class pydm.widgets.drawing.PyDMDrawingLine(parent=None, init_channel=None)[source]ÔÉÅ

Bases: PyDMDrawing

A widget with a line drawn in it. This class inherits from PyDMDrawing.

Parameters:

  • parent (QWidget) ‚Äì The parent widget for the Label

  • init_channel (str, optional) ‚Äì The channel to be used by the widget.

alarm_limit_changed(which: AlarmLimit, new_limit: float) → NoneÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the channel receives new alarm limit values.

Parameters:

  • which (AlarmLimit) ‚Äì Which alarm limit was changed. ‚ÄúHIHI‚Äù, ‚ÄúHIGH‚Äù, ‚ÄúLOW‚Äù, ‚ÄúLOLO‚Äù

  • new_limit (float) ‚Äì New value for the alarm limit

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

channels_for_tools()ÔÉÅ

Returns a list of channels useful for external tools. The default implementation here is just to return self.channels(), but some widgets will want to re-implement this, especially if they have multiple channels, but only one real ‚Äòsignal‚Äô channel.

connected (bool) ‚Äì

connection_changed(connected)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the connection state of the Channel is changed. This callback acts on the connection state to enable/disable the widget and also trigger the change on alarm severity to ALARM_DISCONNECTED.

Parameters:

connected (int) ‚Äì When this value is 0 the channel is disconnected, 1 otherwise.

get_bounds(maxsize=False, force_no_pen=False)ÔÉÅ

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

  • force_no_pen (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True the pen width will not be considered when calculating the bounds.

Returns:

x, y, w, h ‚Äì Tuple with X and Y coordinates followed by the maximum width and height.

Return type:

tuple

paintEngine(self) → QPaintEngineÔÉÅ
paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

Parameters:

event (QPaintEvent) ‚Äì

pyqtConfigure(...)ÔÉÅ

Each keyword argument is either the name of a Qt property or a Qt signal. For properties the property is set to the given value which should be of an appropriate type. For signals the signal is connected to the given value which should be a callable.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

paintEngine(self) → QPaintEngineÔÉÅ
paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

Parameters:

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

get_bounds(maxsize=False, force_no_pen=False)ÔÉÅ

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

  • force_no_pen (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True the pen width will not be considered when calculating the bounds.

Returns:

x, y, w, h ‚Äì Tuple with X and Y coordinates followed by the maximum width and height.

Return type:

tuple

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

get_bounds(maxsize=False, force_no_pen=False)ÔÉÅ

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

get_bounds(maxsize=False, force_no_pen=False)ÔÉÅ

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

class pydm.widgets.drawing.PyDMDrawingIrregularPolygon(parent=None, init_channel=None)[source]ÔÉÅ

Bases: PyDMDrawingPolyline

A widget contains an irregular polygon (arbitrary number of vertices, arbitrary lengths).

This is a special case of the PyDMDrawingPolyline, adding the requirement that the last point is always identical to the first point.

This widget is created for compatibility with MEDM‚Äôs polygon widget.

Parameters:

  • parent (QWidget) ‚Äì The parent widget for the Label

  • init_channel (str, optional) ‚Äì The channel to be used by the widget.

alarm_severity_changed(new_alarm_severity)ÔÉÅ

Callback invoked when the Channel alarm severity is changed. This callback is not processed if the widget has no channel associated with it. This callback handles the composition of the stylesheet to be applied and the call to update to redraw the widget with the needed changes for the new state.

Parameters:

new_alarm_severity (int) ‚Äì The new severity where 0 = NO_ALARM, 1 = MINOR, 2 = MAJOR and 3 = INVALID

get_bounds(maxsize=False, force_no_pen=False)ÔÉÅ

Returns a tuple containing the useful area for the drawing.

Parameters:

  • maxsize (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True, width and height information are based on the maximum inner rectangle dimensions given by `get_inner_max`, otherwise width and height will receive the widget size.

  • force_no_pen (bool, default is False) ‚Äì If True the pen width will not be considered when calculating the bounds.

Returns:

x, y, w, h ‚Äì Tuple with X and Y coordinates followed by the maximum width and height.

tuple

paintEngine(self) → QPaintEngineÔÉÅ
paintEvent(_)ÔÉÅ

Paint events are sent to widgets that need to update themselves, for instance when part of a widget is exposed because a covering widget was moved.

At PyDMDrawing this method handles the alarm painting with parameters from the stylesheet, configures the brush, pen and calls `draw_item` so the specifics can be performed for each of the drawing classes.

Parameters:

event (QPaintEvent) ‚Äì
